<TITLE> Police arrest ex-speaker Humayun Rashid's son </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 3 (bdnews24.com)  Police have arrested Noman Rashid Chowdhury, son of former speaker Humayun Rashid Chowdhury, on a charge of fraud. The arrest was made Wednesday in Dhaka. Hours later, Dhaka metropolitan magistrate Mohammad Hemayet Uddin denied him bail and sent him to jail, pending trial. The charge involves alleged misappropriation of Tk 30 lakh, in a case that was filed in 2002 at Nilphamari Sadar Police Station. However, Mohammadpur Police Station arrested him after receiving a warrant of arrest. The case details were not clear. Mohammadpur police chief Shibli Noman Wednesday told bdnews24.com that they arrested Noman Rashid at his Dhanmondi home. bdnews24.com
